My Meme

The meme I selected for inspiration made fun of when you accidentally see the front cameras perspective on your phone.

I found another cat picture that had similar themes and wrote the necessary text informing the client/user of the joke. I did this by using pipes and the magick library in my R-Script. I found the syntax to be quite strange and unintuitive.

library(magick) 
# Path assets/base_meme.jpg + base_own.jpg
orignalimg <- image_read('assets/base_meme.jpg') # Original Image 
img <- image_blank(554, 554,'white') 
img <-image_read("assets/base_own.jpg") %>% 
  image_append() %>%
  image_annotate("  WHEN U ACCIDENTALLY\nTURN THE FRONTCAM ON",
                 size=30, 
                 color = 'white',
                 location = "+70+50", 
                 weight=600
                 ) %>%  
  image_write(path='my_meme.jpg')

My animated GIF

The animation I created was inspired by examples of filters/effects from the cran.r project. It reads the starting image then applies effects to an array of three images. It then makes use of the morph function to create a transitioning effect. The morph function seems incredibly useful. Magick as a package seems very intuitive especially compared to Open Cv

library(magick)
img <- image_read('assets/download.png')  
img2 <- image_blur(img, 10, 5)
img3 <- image_negate(img2)
anim <- image_resize(c(img3, img2,img), "220x445!") %>% 
  image_background('white') %>% 
  image_morph(20) %>% 
  image_animate() %>%
  image_write(path='my_animation.gif')
